survey_response.review_text: I was having severe stomach ache on Sunday 14 th Feb 21 since 4 PM. I consulted in Emergency clinic of the hosp at 2 AM on night of 14th/15th. There was not much relief. Next day on 15th Feb pain was still continuing and I consulted Dr Prabha Ramadurai at Nano hisp at 1245 PM. She thouroughly examined my stomach area and advised for immediate Ultrasound scan as she suspected inflammation of appendix. She also advised me to consult a surgeon immediately if the appendicitis is confirmed. I underwent the scan at 4 PM and it revealed the same problem. I got admitted at 5 30 PM same day at Fortis hosp and the surgery was done on 16th. The doctor's correct diagnosis and timely advise helped me to take proper action. Thank you Dr Prabha Ramadurai.

Visited her for my mom’s body aches and headache. She prescribed medicines for 10 days **** *** *** ******* ***** ** *** *** ***** ***** **** **** ** *** * ** ***********  We visited her again and after listening to our reason for 2nd visit, she simply said - The body is not responding to medication and I am referring you you Ortho. Plus, she was not very friendly and cut me off several times with random response, while I was explaining my mom’s current state. Very disappointed.

We had gone there with recent reports including MRI scan and blood tests that were prescribed by a remote family doctor. However this doctor didn't pay much attention to that nor was interested in hearing out the symptoms/ patient history and instead chided for showing a report summary on the mobile phone instead of print out.

She then asked to do a few blood tests, some of which were already done and there in the report and suggested that we do the tests and consult with her and she would then suggest whether a neurologist is required.

***** *** ****** *** *** ** *** ***** ** **** *** *** ** ***** **** **** ***** But asking to repeat tests without looking at existing report gave a very bad impression.
Doctor was very friendly. She asked all the questions regarding health issues. She will communivated in English however we are not comfortable with kannada/Tamil/Hindi.
